# $name

AiSOC **responder** plugin generated by `aisoc plugin new`.

## Contract

- `supported_actions` — list of verbs your responder understands.
- `execute(action, params, context)` — returns
  `{"status": "ok" | "skipped" | "error", "detail": ..., "artifact": ...}`.

Always honour `dry_run=true` and return `status="skipped"`. The investigation
timeline relies on this to render an honest record of what was actually done.

## Develop

```bash
aisoc plugin validate plugin.yaml
pytest -v
```

## Publish

```bash
aisoc plugin publish .
```
